			&lt;li&gt;End diff &amp;#8211;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;    I have created a issue regarding this: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3892&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3892&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    No, there is not any alternative for older version. There are very less possibilities of someone using very old OpenSSL library. This issue is negligible, it is just for improving the project.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15406461" author="jking3" created="Wed, 3 Aug 2016 19:16:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jensg&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jensg&quot;&gt;jensg&lt;/a&gt; please review this change to ensure you agree with the preprocessor branch logic and don&apos;t want to do anything more fancy like checking the OpenSSL version that is set in the build environment, or set up something like configure would to check if a system has sscanf_r() &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;for example&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; to detect whether this API is accessible or not.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
